For everyone that is having issues with the sound (no sound) when playing on Home Cinema systems, here's what you can do to fix it. You will have to remove the Header Stripping by remuxing the file (not re-encoding, no quality loss!). Don't worry, it's easy!

1- You will need 'MKVToolnix' (free software) {Google it, first result [bunkus dot org]};

2- click on 'Downloads' link (up there, after 'News');

3- If you use Windows, click on 'Windows' button, under the 'Downloads' title; click on the link 'an installler' or '7zip archive', which one you prefer;

4- install it and open (it's name will be 'mkvmerge GUI'); click on 'File' and then on 'Options';

5- check 'Disable reader removal compression for audio and video tracks by default'; hit 'OK';

6- In 'Input' tab, click on 'add'; select the movie file and open it (you will notice the audio and video tracks in the 'Tracks, chapters and tags' box - leave all checked!);

7- click on 'Start muxing' down there. Just wait a few seconds and a new movie file will be created with NO Header Stripping on the audio;

8- now you will be able to play it on regular Home Cinema players WITH the sound! Enjoy! ;)
